headline: JPMorgan, Delta, Intel, AMD, Adobe, Moderna, Super Micro, and More Stock Market Movers
summary: Stocks fell Tuesday after the latest data from the Bureau of Labor Statistics showed inflation held steady in December as prices for goods and services rose 2.7%.  JPMorgan Chase  fell 4.2%.  Earnings of $4.63 a share fell short of analysts’ calls for $4.85.

headline: Why Moderna Stock Strength Is Only Beginning: Technical Analysis
summary: Moderna stock, depressed for so long, is breaking out—and the gains could keep coming.  Moderna  rounded out a bottom in 2025, and the stock is now putting its foot on the accelerator in 2026.  Wit the stock trading at a trecent $38.50 on Tuesday, a longer term double bottom with handle looks to be forming.

headline: These Stocks Are Today’s Movers: JPMorgan, Delta, L3Harris, Intel, AMD, BNY Mellon, and More
summary: Stock futures were falling Tuesday as investors digested quarterly results from  JPMorgan Chase  and  Delta Air Lines  both of which kicked off the earnings season.  JPMorgan Chase  rose 0.4%.  Although the bank’s profit declined 7% in the fourth quarter, revenue rose on the back of higher fees and interest income.
